Select an image that you want to copy, improve, or inspire to. Select the aspect ratio to be the closest one to the selected image. 
If you don't want any guide picture, select any random one, and then the aspect ratio that you want: you will then set the image_to_image_strenght to 1.0 in the sampler to neutralize the guide picture.

for the workflow to work properly, you should not change the loaders, but feel free to experiment.

With the group bypasser you can turn off some of the features if you don't need them

Set the seed to be fixed or random depending on your needs

Set the controlnet amounts to use them as guides for the image generation: it's important to experiment between the image_to_image_strenght in the sampler, and the controlnet. As of today (october 2024) Flux1 doesn't seems to like controlnet values above 0.3, and the best way to heavily guide an image is by using the image_to_image_strenght

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

A common workflow could be to generate images without the face and hand detailer, without the seed randomizer, so that if you find a good one, then turn on the detailers and finish the workflow; This workflow can also be applied after an initial run with randomization, and upon reviewing the random seed picures, choose the best ones to refine.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The upscale step can be applied in series, or as a stand alone process, by bypassing all the groups except the upscaler and connecting the image load node instead of the flux_image node
